''Fanconi anemia''' is a rare [[gene]]tic disorder. It is a kind of [[anemia]]. People suffering from the disease produce a smaller amount of [[red blood cell|red]] and [[white blood cell]]s. It is named after [[Guido Fanconi]] who first described the disease, in 1929. It should not be confused with [[Fanconi syndrome]]. Fanconi syndrome is a disorder affecting the [[kidney]]s.


